### Converting Characters to and from ASCII

Every character is represented in binary using ASCII encoding:

- "A" = 65, "B" = 66, "C" = 67, ... "Z" = 90

The functions ASC (or ord) and CHR convert between characters and their ASCII decimal values:

```
num = ASC("A")    // puts num = 65
letter = CHR(66)  // puts letter = "B"
```

