### The do...until Loop

The condition is tested at the END of the loop. The loop body always executes at least once.

Pattern:

```
do
    ...
until (continue == "N") OR (continue == "n")
```

Example 6 — powers of 2 quiz:

```
//random(a,b) generates a random integer between a and b
do
    power = random(2, 12)
    powerOf2 = 2^power
    answer = input("What is 2 to the power of ", power)
    if answer == powerOf2 then
        print("Correct, well done")
    else
        print("No, it is ", powerOf2)
    endif
    anotherGo = input("Another go? Answer Y or N: ")
    anotherGo = anotherGo.upper() //converts anotherGo to uppercase
until anotherGo == "N"
```

Note: anotherGo.upper() ensures the loop exits correctly whether the user types "n" or "N".

