### Nested Loops

One loop can be placed inside another (nested loops).

Example 7 — display all multiplication tables from 2 to 12:

```
for table = 2 to 12
    for count = 1 to 12
        product = table * count
        print(table, " x ", count, " = ", product)
    next count
next table
```

The inner loop (count) completes all 12 iterations for each single iteration of the outer loop (table).

