### Functions

Functions are similar to procedures but always return a value. A return statement identifies a subroutine as a function.

Built-in functions already used: asc and chr:

```
letter = chr(68)         // assigns "D" to letter
asciiValue = asc("B")    // assigns 66 to asciiValue
```

Example 10 — user-defined function to convert centimetres to inches:

```
function cms2inches(metric)
    CM_TO_INCH = 2.54
    inches = metric / CM_TO_INCH
    return inches
endfunction
```

Calling the function:

```
HeightMetric = input("Enter your height in centimetres: ")
print("Your height in inches is ", cms2inches(HeightMetric))
```

The return statement sends the result back to the calling code.

