### Using Random Number Generation Functions

Most programming languages provide a random number function. In OCR Exam Reference Language:

```
throw = random(1, 6)
```

This generates a random integer between 1 and 6 (inclusive) — useful for simulating a die throw.

Example 11 — count how many times each name is randomly selected from an array:

```
nameList = ["Anne", "Bob", "Jane", "Vera", "Mabel", "Tony", "Nur"]
totals = [0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0]
numTimes = input("How many names do you want to generate? ")
for i = 1 to numTimes
    index = random(0, 6)
    totals[index] = totals[index] + 1
next i
for i = 0 to 6
    print(nameList[i], totals[i])
next i
```

