### Local and Global Variables

Global variables: declared or used in the main program and recognised throughout the program and any subroutines it calls.

Local variables: declared inside a function or procedure and only exist while that subroutine is executing. They are not recognised anywhere else in the program.

Example — average function with local variable:

```
function average(n1, n2, n3)
    total = n1 + n2 + n3
    avg = total / 3
    return avg
endfunction
```

Calling the function:

```
mean = average(n1, n2, n3)
```

The variable total is local to the function average. Attempting to print total outside the function will cause an error.

