### Advantages of Using Subroutines

Using subroutines to perform specific tasks has many advantages:

- Decomposing a large problem into sub-tasks makes the problem easier to solve
- Each subroutine can be tested separately
- Subroutines can be reused several times within a program
- Subroutines can be stored in a subroutine library and used in different programs
- Several programmers can work on different subroutines simultaneously, speeding up large projects
- If requirements change, only the relevant subroutine needs to be modified, making program maintenance easier

