### Comma-Separated Value (.csv) Files

A CSV file is a text file where commas separate fields on each line, similar to fields in a database record. The filename has the suffix .csv.

Example CSV content:

```
Fred,23,24,27,24
Sally,34,27,30,31
Jimmy,29,30,28,34
Deborah,27,27,26,30
Cynthia,32,35,30,31
Dev,30,25,32,30
Adie,24,17,23,27
```

Spreadsheet programs (e.g. Excel) recognise the CSV format and display each field in a separate column. A CSV file can be processed in exactly the same way as a plain text file, using string handling commands to find the commas and extract the text between them.


